DOC.brief_summary: The purpose study evaluate in-vivo wettability soft contact lens care two different multi-purpose solution two week wear period .
DOC.criteria: 1 . The subject must least 18 year age 80 year age . 2 . The subject must best correct visual acuity 20/30 good eye . 3 . The subject must habitually wear contact lens . 4 . The subject must eye exam within last 12 month . The exam data must available investigator prior first visit . 5 . The subject must normal eye , use ocular medication , ocular infection type , ocular inflammation . 6 . The subject must read understand sign Statement Informed Consent . 7 . The subject must appear able willing adhere instruction set forth clinical protocol . 1 . Ocular systemic allergy disease might interfere contact lens wear . 2 . Systemic disease , autoimmune disease use medication might interfere contact lens wear . 3 . Clinically significant ( FDA Scale grade 3 4 ) corneal edema , corneal vascularization , corneal stain abnormality cornea would contraindicate contact lens wear . 4 . Clinically significant ( FDA Scale grade 3 4 ) tarsal abnormality bulbar injection might interfere contact lens wear . 5 . Any ocular infection . 6 . Pregnancy lactation . 7 . Diabetes 8 . Infectious disease ( e.g . hepatitis , tuberculosis ) 9 . Contagious immunosuppressive disease ( e.g . HIV )
